… As Auditors-General Gather In Abuja To Brainstorm On Efficiency Abuja – President Muhammadu Buhari has said auditing professionals in Nigeria are either compromised or constrained from carrying out their responsibilities of exposing corrupt practices in the country. Buhari said moving forward, he would expect auditing professionals to carry out their jobs without fear or favour, irrespective of the constraints they face. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network He made these remarks while declaring the conference of Auditors – General in Nigeria, with its theme: “Building Government Audit Institutions Nigeria Needs for the 21st Century” opened at the International Conference Centre, Abuja on Tuesday. Details later…